use lsblk to determine device designation
e.g. /dev/sdd

unmount the card if needed
	umount /dev/sdd

zero the data on the card
	sudo dd bs=4M if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdd oflag=sync status=progress
		bs: BYTES to be read/written at a time (block size)
		if: input file
		of: output file
		oflag=sync: use synchronisation I/O for both data and metadata (see "dd --help")
		status=progress: provides progress status to stdout - only works from version 8.24+

write the image to the card
	sudo dd bs=4M if=/path_to_imagefile.img of=/dev/sdd oflag=sync status=progress
